  <prompt>
    Build the `CommandRouter` parser — the entry point for Pillar 8 Command Router.
    Per spec FR-48, the parser MUST run BEFORE agent invocation and emit a structured
    `Intent { command, references[], rawText }` shape that downstream tasks (hard slashes 081,
    soft slashes 082, references resolver 083) consume.

    The parser is a pure TypeScript module in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/CommandRouter.ts`.
    It does NOT call the LLM. It does NOT alter `CapabilityRouter` behavior. It SITS in front of
    the existing conversation send path and produces a normalized intent that tasks 081/082/083
    fan out from.

    Per Q6 the vocabulary is closed at 6 hard slashes (`/clear`, `/new-session`, `/help`,
    `/export`, `/save-to-matter [matterId]`, `/pin`) + 4 soft slashes (`/summarize`, `/draft`,
    `/extract-entities`, `/analyze`) + 3 reference types (`#scope`, `@<entity>`, `#<filename>`).
    The parser tokenizes the input but does NOT execute commands — execution is the
    concern of tasks 081 (hard) + 082 (soft); reference resolution is task 083.

    NFR-11 binding: natural language still flows through unchanged when no slash is detected.
    The parser's failure mode for unrecognized slashes is to return `command: null` so the
    existing `CapabilityRouter` natural-language path handles the input.

    This is a frontend-only task; BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (no .cs files modified).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior TypeScript engineer with Fluent v9 + Spaarke AI Widgets familiarity. Comfortable
    with command-parser design, intent-typing, and frontend integration into a React
    conversation pane without disturbing the existing `SprkChat.onBeforeSendMessage` informational hook.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `CommandRouter.ts` exists at `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/CommandRouter.ts`
    with: (a) typed `Intent` shape; (b) `parse(rawText: string): Intent` function that classifies
    slashes (hard/soft/none) and extracts unresolved references; (c) unit tests covering each
    command + reference shape + composition + natural-language passthrough; (d) zero LLM calls
    in the parse path; (e) clean module exports for downstream tasks. NFR-11 backward compat
    verified: natural language sends still reach `CapabilityRouter` unchanged when no slash present.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
