    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Intent shape" location="src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/CommandRouter.ts (new)">
        Export `interface Intent { command: SlashCommand | null; references: Reference[]; rawText: string; isHardSlash: boolean; isSoftSlash: boolean; }`.
        Pure function `parse(rawText: string): Intent`. No side effects, no async, no network.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Slash vocabulary closed" location="Q6 + spec FR-49/FR-50">
        Hard: `/clear`, `/new-session`, `/help`, `/export`, `/save-to-matter`, `/pin`. Soft: `/summarize`, `/draft`, `/extract-entities`, `/analyze`. Reference shapes: `#scope`, `@<entity>`, `#<filename>`. Use string-literal union type.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Check context usage. Output: "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — Foundational Pillar 8 parser; gates 4 downstream Phase D tasks; spec FR-48 binding". Read project CLAUDE.md §Pillar 8 + spec.md FR-48–54.
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` and confirm task 080 status is 🔲, dependencies (078 Phase C exit gate) are ✅. Verify Phase C is complete before starting. Update `current-task.md` to task 080.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read SPAARKEAI-COMPONENT-MODEL.md + COMPONENT-MODEL §Conversation. Inspect `ConversationPane.tsx` to understand the existing send-message hook surface. Read the project CLAUDE.md §Pillar 8 binding rules.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Author Intent Type + Parser">
      Create `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/CommandRouter.ts`. Define `Intent` type, slash command union, reference shape. Implement `parse(rawText: string): Intent` with: hard-slash detection, soft-slash detection, reference extraction (`#`/`@`), natural-language passthrough (returns `command: null`).
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Unit Tests">
      Create `CommandRouter.test.ts`. Cover: each hard slash, each soft slash, each reference shape, composition (`/summarize #file.docx`), unrecognized slash → passthrough, natural language → passthrough, empty input. Use existing project test runner (vitest / jest per `SpaarkeAi/` convention).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="NFR-11 Backward Compat Test">
      Add a specific regression test verifying that input without a slash returns `{ command: null, references: [], rawText, isHardSlash: false, isSoftSlash: false }` so the downstream send path can fall through to `CapabilityRouter` unchanged.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Wire-Up Stub (no behavior change yet)">
      Add an import + `const intent = parse(message)` call inside `ConversationPane.tsx` at the send-message boundary BUT do NOT branch behavior yet. Intent is captured + logged via existing telemetry (no new ADR-015 events; tool name + decision only would be added by 081/082). This validates the parser is reachable; behavior changes land in 081/082/083.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Build Verification">
      Run `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` + `npm run build` in `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/` per CLAUDE.md §11 (avoid `npm ci`). Run the test suite. Confirm zero TypeScript errors.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through each &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below. Confirm each is testable + green.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against CommandRouter.ts + tests. Run `adr-check` against same; verify ADR-029 (size 0 MB), ADR-030 (no 5th channel), NFR-11 (backward compat), NFR-01 (conversational primacy preserved). Both gates MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status to `complete`. Update TASK-INDEX.md: 080 🔲 → ✅. Reset `current-task.md` to task 081. Note BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB. Report completion + downstream unblock list (081, 082, 083, 084, 086).
    </step>
  </steps>

